# Trivy IaC findings that have been reviewed and consciously accepted.
# Each entry must carry a justification. Re-review periodically.

# AWS-0104: Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to 0.0.0.0/0.
# Accepted: SAP NetWeaver/HANA hosts require broad outbound connectivity for OS
# patching, SAP software downloads, SSM Session Manager, EFS, and AWS service
# endpoints. Operators who run in a fully private/proxied network can tighten
# egress in their own fork or via the instance security groups. Tracked as a
# future enhancement (make egress CIDRs a variable) in REHAUL_PLAYBOOK.md.
AWS-0104
